data.enText: to hear, especially by accident, a conversation in which you are not involved

data.chText: 我们低声交谈，以免别人听到。
data.enText: We talked quietly so as not to be overheard.

data.chText: 我在公共汽车上无意中听到两个男孩的谈话。
data.enText: I overheard a conversation between two boys on the bus.

data.chText: 我们碰巧听到他们吵嘴。
我偶然听见他说他要去法国。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+不带to的不定式

data.enText: I overheard him say he was going to France.

simple_means.memory_skill: over 在…之上，凌驾 + hear 听 → 意料之外听到 → 无意中听到

synonyms.bx: 指声音进入耳内，侧重于听的能力和结果，但不含注意之意。

ex.chText: 上课时他一向专心听老师讲课。
ex.enText: He always listens to the teachers attentively in class.

ex.chText: 他听了，但什么也没听见。
ex.enText: He listened but didn't hear anything.

synonyms.bx: 指有意识地倾听，强调行为的过程。

ex.chText: 我偶然听到他们说，他们很不快乐。
ex.enText: I overheard them saying they were unhappy.

ex.chText: 他无意中听到管理层在讨论加薪的事。
ex.enText: He overheard the management discussing pay rises.

synonyms.bx: 多指在他人不注意或不知道的情况下偶然听到谈话的内容。

tr: hear, usually without the knowledge of the speakers
example: We overheard the conversation at the next table

value.def: If you overhear someone, you hear what they are saying when they are not talking to you and they do not know that you are listening.

example.ex: I overheard two doctors discussing my case.
example.tran: 我无意中听到两位医生讨论我的病情。

value.tran: 偶然听到；无意中听到；偷听到
